03/01/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- Two passenger trains collided in northwest Turkey early on Sunday (January 3rd) killing one of the drivers and injuring at least four people. 
The express trains travelling between Istanbul and Eskisehir collided at around 10 AM local time. 
According to initial reports, the accident happened when one of the drivers ignored a signal warning. 
(BBC, AFP, CNN Turk - 03/01/10)
